### Implementation for AIUsageMonitor

- [X] T011 [Monitor-Impl] Create `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts` class extending EventEmitter
  - Constructor: Accept UsageLogger, CostBudgetEnforcer, MultiSessionBridgeWatcher
  - Define event types: 'usage-update' with UsageUpdateEvent payload
  - Initialize private fields: watcher, polling timer, cache, last session ID
- [X] T012 [Monitor-Impl] Implement `getUsageData(period)` method in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Determine date range for period (current/today/week)
  - Call `usageLogger.getUsageSummary(fromDate, toDate)` with date filters
  - Map UsageLogger format to AIUsageData:
    - UsageLogger returns { byProvider: { anthropic: { tokens, costUsd, sessions } } }
    - AIUsageData needs { providers: [{ providerId, inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd }] }
    - If UsageLogger only provides total tokens, estimate split: 60% input, 40% output
    - Use actual inputTokens/outputTokens if available in raw log entries
  - Calculate costs using shared config/pricing.ts COST_PER_1K_TOKENS rates
  - Formula: (inputTokens / 1_000_000) * inputRatePerM + (outputTokens / 1_000_000) * outputRatePerM
  - For 'current' period: filter by sessionId from MultiSessionBridgeWatcher
  - For 'current' period: add budget fields from CostBudgetEnforcer.getSnapshot()
  - Implement 5s cache TTL (return cached if within TTL)
- [ ] T013 [Monitor-Impl] Implement FileSystemWatcher for council-usage.jsonl in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Create RelativePattern for `.specify/logs/council-usage.jsonl`
  - Call `vscode.workspace.createFileSystemWatcher(pattern)`
  - Subscribe to `onDidChange` and `onDidCreate` events
  - On event: clear cache, call getUsageData() for all periods, emit 'usage-update'
  - Guard against duplicate watchers (check if watcher already exists)
  - Store watcher instance for later disposal
- [ ] T014 [Monitor-Impl] Implement periodic polling (5s interval) in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - `startMonitoring()`: Create setInterval calling getUsageData() every 5000ms
  - Only start polling if file watcher is active (hybrid approach)
  - Emit 'usage-update' event after each poll with trigger='polling'
  - Guard against duplicate intervals (clear existing before creating new)
  - Store interval ID for later disposal
- [ ] T015 [Monitor-Impl] Implement session detection integration in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Subscribe to MultiSessionBridgeWatcher 'bridge-update' events
  - Extract sessionId from BridgeData for "Current Session" filtering
  - Emit 'usage-update' when active session changes (session ID differs)
  - Store subscription for later unsubscription
- [ ] T016 [Monitor-Impl] Implement `forceRefresh()` method in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Clear cache (set cacheTimestamp to 0)
  - Call getUsageData() for all periods
  - Emit 'usage-update' event with trigger='manual'
- [ ] T017 [Monitor-Impl] Implement `dispose()` for cleanup in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Dispose file watcher if active: `watcher?.dispose()`
  - Clear polling interval if active: `clearInterval(pollingTimer)`
  - Unsubscribe from MultiSessionBridgeWatcher events
  - Clear cache and reset state
  - Mark as disposed to prevent reuse

**Checkpoint**: AIUsageMonitor service complete - all tests passing

