  - Use Gofer's logging infrastructure (if available)
- [ ] T062 Debounce file watcher events in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Multiple file writes within 100ms should trigger only one event (debounce window)
  - Use setTimeout to delay event emission by 100ms (more aggressive than spec's <500ms requirement)
  - Clear timeout if another write occurs within window (debounce pattern)
  - Max latency: 200ms file write + 100ms debounce + 100ms render = 400ms (exceeds spec target)
  - Reduces redundant panel refreshes while maintaining real-time feel
  - Note: Spec requires <500ms file watch latency; this implementation achieves <400ms
- [ ] T063 Cache usage data to avoid re-parsing in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Already implemented in T012 (5s cache TTL)
  - Verify cache works: getUsageData() returns cached data within TTL
  - Verify cache clears on file change or forceRefresh()
- [ ] T064 [P] Add JSDoc comments to public methods in `extension/src/aiUsageProvider.ts`
  - Document getChildren() parameters and return type
  - Document getTreeItem() parameters and return type
  - Document refresh() purpose and when it's called
  - Follow existing Gofer JSDoc style
- [ ] T065 [P] Add JSDoc comments to public methods in `extension/src/autonomous/AIUsageMonitor.ts`
  - Document getUsageData() parameters, return type, caching behavior
  - Document startMonitoring() side effects (watchers, timers)
  - Document stopMonitoring() cleanup guarantees
  - Document events emitted and their payloads
- [ ] T066 [P] Add JSDoc comments to public methods in `extension/src/ui/AIUsageStatusBar.ts`
  - Document connect() integration with monitor
  - Document updateDisplay() parameters and behavior
  - Document dispose() cleanup guarantees

**Checkpoint**: All polish tasks complete, code documented

