## Dependencies & Execution Order

### Phase Dependencies

- **Phase 1 (Setup)**: No dependencies - can start immediately
- **Phase 2 (AIUsageMonitor)**: Depends on Phase 1 (types, fixtures) - ~15% can run in parallel
- **Phase 3 (US1)**: Depends on Phase 2 (monitor service) - TreeDataProvider needs monitor events
- **Phase 4 (US2)**: Depends on Phase 2 (monitor service) - time period filtering in monitor
- **Phase 5 (US3)**: Depends on Phase 2 (monitor service) - budget integration in monitor
- **Phase 6 (US4)**: Depends on Phase 2 (monitor service) - status bar subscribes to monitor events
- **Phase 7 (Integration)**: Depends on Phases 2-6 (all components built)
- **Phase 8 (Polish)**: Depends on Phase 7 (integration complete)

### User Story Dependencies

- **US1 (P1)**: Depends on Phase 2 (AIUsageMonitor) - No dependencies on other user stories
- **US2 (P1)**: Depends on Phase 2 (AIUsageMonitor) - Can run in parallel with US1 (different implementation areas)
- **US3 (P2)**: Depends on Phase 2 (AIUsageMonitor) - Can run in parallel with US1/US2 (budget logic in monitor)
- **US4 (P2)**: Depends on Phase 2 (AIUsageMonitor) - Can run in parallel with US1/US2/US3 (separate status bar component)

### Parallel Opportunities

**Phase 1 (Setup)**: T002, T003, T004, T005 can run in parallel (different files)

**Phase 2 (Tests)**: T006, T007, T008, T009, T010 can run in parallel (different test files)

**Phase 3 (US1 Tests)**: T018, T019, T020 can run in parallel (different test files)

**Phase 4 (US2 Tests)**: T026, T027, T028 can run in parallel (different test files)

**Phase 5 (US3 Tests)**: T032, T033 can run in parallel (different test files)

**Phase 6 (US4 Tests)**: T037, T038, T039, T040 can run in parallel (different test files)

**Phase 6 (US4 Implementation)**: T041, T044 can run in parallel (status bar class vs command registration)

**Phase 7 (Integration Tests)**: T046, T047, T048, T049 can run in parallel (independent test scenarios)

**Phase 8 (Polish)**: T056, T057, T058, T059, T060, T061, T064, T065, T066 can run in parallel (different files/concerns)

### Critical Path

Longest dependency chain (minimum time to complete):

1. T001 (types) → T011 (AIUsageMonitor class) → T012-T017 (monitor implementation)
2. T021 (AIUsageProvider class) → T022-T025 (provider implementation)
3. T050-T055 (integration)
4. T056-T066 (polish)

**Estimated critical path**: 12-18 hours sequential, 8-12 hours with parallelization

